Buttigieg even edges Beto O'Rourke, the former House member from El Paso, Texas, who challenged and narrowly lost a Senate bid to Ted Cruz last November.
The result is that he now leads the second tier of candidates — and could well surpass Beto in the contest to reboot Obamaism.
Journalists, activists, pundits, intellectuals — all of them, myself very much included, think that political campaigns should focus on policy.
This is the sunny side of the multicultural identity politics that defines the Democratic Party more thoroughly with each electoral cycle.
Put in a less sneering tone, one might say that Buttigieg hopes to be many things to many kinds of people.